{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_017vWUwNnjcxGkD3nJMCigX3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Kc6MDBjCXcaytDSGYcmVqq","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is pure manifest validation logic—no module execution, no I/O, no runtime state. The failure boundary is whether the validator correctly checks for required fields. A mock manifest object is sufficient to trigger validation and assert rejection. Mocking cannot miss this failure because there's no external behavior to hide; the validator either checks the field or it doesn't.","test_description":"Create mock manifest objects each missing one required field (name, version, dependencies, onLoad). Pass each through the manifest validator and assert it rejects with a clear error message identifying the missing field. Verify no attempt is made to import or execute the plugin module.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.85,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's onLoad hook is called before plugin A's.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Although dependency ordering is algorithmically testable, the real failure boundary is whether hooks execute in the correct order given Node.js module execution semantics. A unit test with mocked imports might verify the topological sort, but would miss real failures: async module execution, require() caching behavior, or race conditions in actual hook invocation. We must observe real module files being imported and real onLoad invocations to catch production failures.","test_description":"Create two real plugin modules with exported onLoad functions that append themselves to a shared execution log. Configure A to declare B as a dependency. Run the loader and verify the log shows B's onLoad completed before A's began. Repeat with three plugins in a chain (C→B→A) to verify transitive ordering.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"While cycle detection itself is a unit-testable graph algorithm, the behavior \"loads neither\" is not. A unit test verifying the algorithm alone would miss the failure where the loader detects the cycle but then incorrectly initializes one or both plugins anyway. We must verify the complete behavior: cycle detected + zero onLoad invocations + no plugin state changes. This requires real plugins and observable proof they were never invoked.","test_description":"Create two real plugin modules A and B with mutual dependencies, each exporting an onLoad that increments a counter and writes to a log file. Run the loader, verify it returns a cycle error. Assert the counter was never incremented and the log file was never written. Verify the error message clearly names the cycle (A→B→A).","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's onLoad hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This tests the sequence of Node.js module execution and hook timing. The failure boundary is whether the loader correctly waits for the module to be fully loaded (including top-level side effects) before calling onLoad. Mocking the require/import would always succeed synchronously and hide real timing bugs. Actual failures would involve async module initialization, top-level module code with side effects, or improper Promise handling. Only real modules expose this.","test_description":"Create a plugin module that records a unique flag in a shared registry during top-level execution, then exports an onLoad hook. Run the loader against a configuration that expects this flag to exist before onLoad is called. Verify that when onLoad executes, the flag is present. Also test with async top-level code (e.g., a module that awaits a promise during require) to ensure the loader waits for async module initialization.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its onLoad hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This tests error isolation across a plugin dependency graph. A unit test of error handling in isolation would miss whether the loader correctly skips dependents while continuing independents. The real failure boundary is: does the loader halt prematurely? Does it confuse dependency direction? Does it leave the system in an inconsistent state? These can only be verified with multiple real plugins, real dependencies, and observable proof of which plugins initialized. Mocking would hide dependency-driven failures.","test_description":"Create three real plugins: A (independent, succeeds), B (independent, throws in onLoad), and C (depends on B, never reached). Run the loader, capture all errors and logs. Verify A's onLoad was invoked and completed successfully, B's onLoad threw and the error was logged, and C's onLoad was never called. Verify A is fully functional afterward and C's state was not modified. Test with B throwing synchronously and asynchronously to catch both error paths.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13913,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13913},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ce535fc9-6b6f-4522-9861-39f788e40a94","uuid":"ef83e6b6-7bbe-42b8-8fc3-85d75e1dbb04"}
